            "answer_text": "They are all heavily mixed populations with Romans being a common element in all of their populations (to various degrees) Spain: Romans, Celts, Visgoths, Iberians, Arabs, Berbers, Sephardic Jews, Sub-Saharan Africans, Greeks, Phoencians , Carthiginians, Persians Portugal: Romans, Celts, Visgoths, Iberians, Arabs, Berbers, Sephardic Jews, Sub-Saharan Africans Southern Italy & Sicily: Greeks, Romans, Italic Tribes, Vikings, Germanic People, Arabs, Turks, Phoenicians, Carthiginians, Slavs France: Romans, Celts and Germanic Peoples. There\u2019s a limited Mediterranean component in the southern coast as well. I don\u2019t know much about the genetic makeup of northern/central Italy besides Italic Tribes/Romans . But from my research, Modern Day Italians followed by The Portuguese have the most Roman ancestry (according to genetic testing). Both Spain and Portugal have the most Arab/Berber and Sub-Saharan African genes im Europe. SomeSlavs were bought as slaves by the Moors to Spain and Portugal and to a lesser extent Sicily ",
